And that's where it starts drilling really hard. Great!
Her passive-aggressive way of turning my air purifier all the way up makes me uncomfortable, but it smells like sawdust, so it's justified even if it's an anti-mask. And besides, I really need to protect myself, don't I??
I really want to go back to bed, but I can't until he leaves.
The positive side is that I finally finished re-reading Chapter 4!
Chapter five is long, but there's big suspense. Good work.
Working on replacing characters... ➡️  ellipsis character, and there are 54 of them in this chapter 😅
But still, I insist. The most natural speeches are usually fragmented, especially when people let themselves be carried away by their emotions.
The craftsman is vacuuming. Hopefully, he will finish soon.
He went out (as far as I can hear) to cut something. So I took a look to see where he was at. He's not even close to being done :(<-/p>
Only 7 pages left for Chapter five. It's still my favorite chapter, and it's quite polished. Just some formatting tweaks and minor changes to switch to active voice and improve conciseness. That said, I could use a break and a cup of tea, but the guy is still fiddling around in my kitchen.
He's just started vacuuming again. I hope that's a good sign.
The craftsman has gone!
He told me he had quoted the whole floor, but the owners were tight and only paid for the small damaged area near the door. It's much better.
The house is airing out, and my air purifier is running in the kitchen while I enjoy a cup of tea in the garden!
